We have
\begin{equation}
    \frac{d^2 x}{dt^2} = \frac{d}{dt} \left(\frac{dx}{dt}\right) = \frac{dv}{dt} = \frac{dv}{dx} \cdot \frac{dx}{dt} = v \frac{dv}{dx}
\end{equation}

Thus,
\begin{equation}
    v \frac{dv}{dx} = -g - kv^2
\end{equation}

Integrating, we have
\begin{equation}
    \frac{1}{2k} \int \frac{d(v^2)}{(g/k) + v^2} = - \int dx
\end{equation}

Integrating, we obtain
\begin{equation}
    \ln \left(\frac{g/k + v^2}{c}\right) = -2kx \quad \text{or} \quad \frac{g}{k} + v^2 = c e^{-2kx}
\end{equation}

When $x = 0$, $v = u$; thus, $c = \frac{g}{k} + u^2$ and writing $\frac{g}{k} = V^2$, we have
\begin{equation}
    \frac{V^2 + v^2}{V^2 + u^2} = e^{-2gx/V^2}
\end{equation}

