\end{align}

If $\mathbf{v}_1$ and $\mathbf{v}_2$ are to be perpendicular to each other, then $\mathbf{v}_1 \cdot \mathbf{v}_2 = 0$. Therefore, we have:

\begin{align*}
    (u_1 \hat{\imath} - gt \hat{\jmath}) \cdot (-u_2 \hat{\imath} - gt \hat{\jmath}) &= 0 \\
    \Rightarrow -u_1 u_2 + g^2 t^2 &= 0 \\
    \Rightarrow t &= \frac{1}{g} \sqrt{u_1 u_2} \tag{3}
\end{align*}

The position vectors are:

\begin{align}
    \mathbf{r}_1 &= u_1 t \hat{\imath} - \frac{1}{2} gt^2 \hat{\jmath} \\
